The paper discusses the assessment of data quality in Linked Open Data, which is a topic related to databases (cs.DB). The use of probabilistic techniques such as Reservoir Sampling and Bloom Filters suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The evaluation of the performance and accuracy of the implementation suggests a focus on deep learning (cs.DL) and software engineering (cs.SE).
